  "texts": [
    "The initial is the consonant part at the beginning of a Chinese character.",
    "According to whether the vocal cords are vibrating, the consonants can be divided into voiceless and voiced consonants (Chen et al. 2019).",
    "The finals utilize themselves as independent Chinese syllables.",
    "But in most cases, the finals are located behind the initials and together with the initials to form a compound syllable (Social Sciences 2012).",
    "Moreover, tone changes in dialect determine the pronunciation variations of the corresponding syllables."
  ],
